Rating: 3
This was a great 4th of July dish. Soaking the chicken in the sugar & salt gave the chicken a unique tenderness & flavor. I used individual pieces of chicken instead of the half birds and used a local BBQ sauce and rub (I didn't have time to order Clarks). Cooking time at 300 in a gas oven was about 1 hour & 15 minutes. There were no "juices" to baste as the recipe recommends but I slathered bbq sauce on the pieces a few times during the cooking process. Not only did it taste great but I was able to make it a couple of hours in advance of our dinner. So I spent more time with family & friends than working over the food - always a plus! I would make this again for a crowd anytime.

Rating: 3
