Rating: 4
I have been making this recipe since it was first published in 1995, my copy of that issue is very worn. I use the Rub and Mop from CHILI-RUBBED CHICKEN WITH BARBECUE TABLE MOP recipe and BBQ the chicken. Each recipe is good on its own but beyond compare when combined.

Rating: 3
I did not use the Clark's rub or sauce, but marinating the chicken in the brown sugar mixture really kept it moist. Very good. I used the molasses beer barbecue sauce and a roasted garlic rub. It was a beg hit at our Memorial Day PicNic.

Rating: 4
This recipe is excellent - the chicken is extremely moist. My 2 year old son loves it - it is also easy for babies to chew. I use another spice rub recipe with paprike, brown sugar, etc.

Rating: 4
I've made this recipe numerous times for large crowds, and it's always a hit. Very moist and delicious chicken. I found that using free-range chicken produced the best results.